   3.820316448585617*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e2fc3caa-2fc9-49d7-af9a-\
a28e90101162"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["LINE PLOTS:",
 FontWeight->"Bold"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8203164656387453`*^9, 
  3.8203164713825927`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e538afe2-7d0f-4004-a2d8-\
3135b2c25267"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Make a line plot showing the population changes over time for India, China, \
and the United States. Each point in the plot indicates by how much the \
population increased compared to the previous year. Hint: look up the \
definition of the function ",
 StyleBox["Differences",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Compare with the population plots."
}], "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7878468121278057`*^9, 3.7878468742957344`*^9}, {
  3.787846910015852*^9, 3.78784697596779*^9}, {3.8203179481026244`*^9, 
  3.8203179582298403`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ac4495e0-74cb-4777-b875-\
ac74980aa632"],

Cell["\<\
Create a function that accepts a list of countries, and creates a line plot \
of population over time for those countries, starting in 1920 until the \
present day.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7878468121278057`*^9, 3.7878468742957344`*^9}, {
  3.787846910015852*^9, 3.78784692517557*^9}, {3.7878472669523787`*^9, 
  3.787847318532794*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c1c016b6-11dc-45d6-8f4d-\
f9e017f5063c"],

Cell["\<\
Modify the function above to plot symbols as well as lines, and associate \
each symbol with a tooltip that displays the GDP per capita at that time.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7878468121278057`*^9, 3.7878468742957344`*^9}, {
  3.787846910015852*^9, 3.78784692517557*^9}, {3.7878472669523787`*^9, 
